Date of Birth: April 2, 1821<br/>
Birthplace: Richmond, Massachusetts, USA<br/>
Ordained apostle: February 12, 1849<br/>
Death: December 9, 1899<br/>
<br/>
Born April 2, 1821, at Richmond, Berkshire Co., Massachusetts, to Phinehas Richards and Wealthy Dewey. Ordained apostle Feb. 12, 1849, by Heber C. Kimball, at age 27; sustained as president of the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles Sept. 13, 1898; died Dec. 9, 1899, at Ogden, Weber Co., Utah, at age 78.